# ROI Command Vocabulary (roi/ subtree scope)

ROI is a **skill-driven** lifecycle. There is no MCP server. Each `roi:*`
command opens a SKILL.md under `skills/` and follows its procedure.
Skills shell to `node scripts/lifecycle.mjs <verb>` (paths relative to the
ROI package root) to read and persist durable state in SQLite
(`.data/roi.sqlite`).

This rule scopes the same vocabulary to the `roi/` subtree. The
workspace-level rule lives at `../../.cursor/rules/roi-commands.mdc`.

## Commands → Skills

| Command | Stage | Canonical skill |
|---|---|---|
| `roi:start [goal]` | Open mission | `skills/roi-start/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:work [goal]` | Alias for `roi:start` | `skills/roi-work/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:clarify` | Refine brief | `skills/roi-clarify/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:brief` | Alias for `roi:clarify` | `skills/roi-brief/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:source` | Record research | `skills/roi-source/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:research` | Alias for `roi:source` | `skills/roi-research/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:outline` | Generate plans | `skills/roi-outline/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:plan` | Alias for `roi:outline` | `skills/roi-plan/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:go [goal]` | Implement plans | `skills/roi-go/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:draft` | Open run | `skills/roi-draft/SKILL.md` |
